@startuml seq-notification-flow
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Notification Creation and Delivery Flow

participant "System Event\n(OrderService,\nMeetingService)" as SysEvent
participant "NotificationDispatcher" as Dispatcher
participant "NotificationsAPI\n/api/notifications" as NotifAPI
participant "NotificationService" as NotifSvc
database "PostgreSQL\nnotifications.notifications" as DB
participant "Admin Dashboard" as AdminApp
actor Admin

== Notification Creation ==

SysEvent -> Dispatcher : Event: order_placed\n{ orderId, customerId }
Dispatcher -> Dispatcher : Build notification payload
Dispatcher -> NotifAPI : POST /api/notifications\n{ recipientId: adminId,\ntype: 'order',\nmessage: 'New order #1042 placed' }
NotifAPI -> NotifSvc : Create notification
NotifSvc -> DB : INSERT INTO notifications\n(recipientId, type, message, read=false)
DB --> NotifSvc : notification record
NotifSvc --> NotifAPI : created notification
NotifAPI --> Dispatcher : 201 Created

== Notification Retrieval ==

Admin -> AdminApp : Open notifications page
AdminApp -> NotifAPI : GET /api/notifications\n?recipientId={adminId}
NotifAPI -> NotifSvc : Fetch by recipientId
NotifSvc -> DB : SELECT * FROM notifications\nWHERE recipient_id=?\nORDER BY created_at DESC
DB --> NotifSvc : notification list
NotifSvc --> NotifAPI : notifications[]
NotifAPI --> AdminApp : 200 OK — notification list
AdminApp --> Admin : Display unread notifications

== Mark as Read ==

Admin -> AdminApp : Click notification
AdminApp -> NotifAPI : PUT /api/notifications/{id}\n{ read: true }
NotifAPI -> NotifSvc : Update read status
NotifSvc -> DB : UPDATE notifications\nSET read=true WHERE id=?
DB --> NotifSvc : updated
NotifSvc --> NotifAPI : updated notification
NotifAPI --> AdminApp : 200 OK
AdminApp --> Admin : Notification marked as read

@enduml
